.TH vdf_read_file 3

.SH NAME
vdf_read_file

.SH LIBRARY
Valve Data Format Parser Library (libvdfc)

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <vdfc/vdf.h>

VDFcode vdf_read_file(const char *filename, char **buffer, size_t *size);

.SH DESCRIPTION
Read a file into a newly allocated null-terminated buffer.

Caller must free() the buffer. \fB`out_size`\fR is optional. If non-NULL,
receives the file size in bytes (excluding the trailing null terminator).

.SH RETURN VALUE
Upon a successful read, returns \fB`VDF_OK`\fR.
Otherwise, returns an error code.

.SH ERRORS
.PP
\fB`VDF_ERR_OPEN`\fR: Failed to open the input file.
.PP
\fB`VDF_ERR_IO`\fR: Read/seek error while accessing the file.
.PP
\fB`VDF_ERR_MALLOC`\fR: Memory allocation failure.

